Conference Paper: 
--Wenjun Li and et al, “TabTree: A TSS-assisted Bit-selecting Tree Scheme for Packet Classification with Balanced Rule Mapping” In ACM/IEEE Symposium on Architectures for Networking and Communications Systems (ANCS), 2019.

TabTree Version 1.0:
Released on www.wenjunli.com/TabTree
Finished by Wenjun Li (Designer) and Ting Huang (Coder, Under the guidance of Wenjun Li)  
Tested on Ubuntu 16.04.4 LTS 

Requirement:
g++ at least version 4.9.

Installation: make
How to run: ./main [options]

Usage:
./main [-b bucketSize][-t threshold(assume T_SA=T_DA)][-r ruleset][-e trace]

Try now:
./main 
or 
./main -b 4 -t 16 -r ./fw_1k -e ./fw_1k_trace 

If you have any questions, feel free to contact with me. 
For the future work, please pay attention to the website: www.wenjunli.com

Wenjun Li
Peking University
